===Music===
*Al Capone is referenced heavily in [[Prodigy (rapper)|Prodigy]]'s track &quot;Al Capone Zone&quot;,&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://new.music.yahoo.com/alchemist/tracks/al-capone-zone--207389271 |title=Al Capone Zone &amp;#124; Alchemist Song |publisher=New.music.yahoo.com |date= |accessdate=2011-01-27}}&lt;/ref&gt; produced by [[The Alchemist]] and featuring [[Keak Da Sneak]].
*Al Capone transcribed a love song called ''[[Madonna Mia]]'' while in prison. In May 2009, his rendition of the song was recorded for the first time in history. {{citation needed|date=December 2010}}

