In addition, the [[Instituto de Meteorologia]] has identified the following weather extremes:
* Highest minimum air temperature: {{convert|24.3|°C|F|abbr=on}}, in Angra do Heroísmo, Terceira (30/06/1996)
* Lowest minimum air temperature: {{convert|-3.5|°C|F|abbr=on}}, in Chã das Lagoinhos, São Miguel (02/01/1973)
* Highest maximum air temperature: {{convert|32.1|°C|F|abbr=on}}, in Madalena, Pico (07/09/1985)
* Lowest maximum air temperature: {{convert|4.0|°C|F|abbr=on}}, Chã das Lagoinhas, São Miguel (20/02/1972)
* Maximum precipitation in 24 hours: {{convert|27.6|cm|2|abbr=on|lk=out}}, Furnas, São Miguel (03/10/1974)
* Maximum wind speed: &gt;168&amp;nbsp;km/hour, Angra do Heroísmo, (Terceira 02/11/1995)&lt;ref&gt;Maximum wind speed recorded during [[Hurricane Tanya (1995)]], Institute of Meteorology, IP Portugal [http://www.meteo.pt/pt/oclima/extremos/]&lt;/ref&gt;

===Human geography===
The Azores are divided into 19 municipalities ({{lang|pt|''concelhos''}}); each municipality is further divided into parishes ({{lang|pt|''freguesias''}}), of which there is a [[List of parishes of Portugal|total of 156]] in all of the Azores.  The municipalities, by island, are:

