==Leadership==
*President: [[Gianfranco Fini]] (1995–2008), [[Ignazio La Russa]] (''regent'', 2008–2009)
**Coordinator: [[Maurizio Gasparri]] (1995–1998), [[Ignazio La Russa]] (2003–2005)
**Spokesman: [[Francesco Storace]] (1995–1997), [[Adolfo Urso]] (1997–2001), [[Antonio Landolfi]] (2001–2005), [[Andrea Ronchi]] (2005–2009)
**Head of Political Secretariat: [[Donato Lamorte]] (1995–2002), [[Andrea Ronchi]] (2002–2004), [[Carmelo Briguglio]] (2002–2004), [[Donato Lamorte]] (2004–2009)
*President of National Assembly: [[Domenico Fisichella]] (1995–2005), [[Marcello Perina]] (2005–2006), [[Francesco Servello]] (2006–2009)
*Organizational Coordinator: [[Giuseppe Tatarella]] (1995–1998), [[Altero Matteoli]] (1998–2002), [[Donato Lamorte]] (2002–2004), [[Italo Bocchino]] (2004–2005), [[Marco Martinelli (politician)|Marco Martinelli]] (2005–2009)
*Administrative Secretary: [[Francesco Pontone]] (1995–2009)

*Party Leader at the [[Italian Chamber of Deputies|Chamber of Deputies]]: [[Raffaele Valensise]] (1994–1995), [[Giuseppe Tatarella]] (1995–1998), [[Gustavo Selva]] (1998–2001), [[Ignazio La Russa]] (2001–2003), [[Gian Franco Anedda]] (2003–2004), [[Iganzio La Russa]] (2004–2008), [[Italo Bocchino]] (deputy-leader of [[People of Freedom|PdL]]'s group, 2008–2009)
*Party Leader at the [[Italian Senate|Senate]]: [[Giulio Maceratini]] (1994–2001), [[Domenico Nania]] (2001–2006), [[Altero Matteoli]] (2006–2008), [[Maurizio Gasparri]] (leader of [[People of Freedom|PdL]]'s group, 2008–2009)
*Party Leader at the [[European Parliament]]: [[Cristiana Muscardini]] (1994–2004), [[Roberta Angelilli]] (2004–2009)

